title: (p,pn) and (p,2n) cross sections in medium weight elements.

x4codes.hlp: Oak Ridge National Laboratory, Oak Ridge, TN, United States of America
Oak Ridge National Laboratory, Oak Ridge, TN, United States of America

x4freetext: . 86 inch pole face diameter.
Ratios of activation cross sections were measured from
different target combinations. For several nuclides
absolute disintegration rates were measured by
comparison with calibrated standards. Combining these
measurements relative cross sections for all reactions
were obtained. Absolute cross sections were obtained
by measuring the proton current by means of the known
absolute cross sections for Cu-63(P,N)Zn-63. Most of
the cross sections were determined from at least two
independent ratios. Therefore other target
combinations than given under sample may be used.
No information about the decay data used is given.
The reproducibility of the data is about 7%.
The relative cross sections may be uncertain by as
much as 15%.  In addition the absolute calibration of
the cross sections may be in error by about 15%.
Table I of Phys.Rev.99(1955)718.
